<br>
A: This link takes you to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>your</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> control center, the place where <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>you</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> decide your ezboard preferences.  <br>
<br>
I'll break it down and note the differences for various account types<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The My Account page</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If you are a local user, you will see a link to this community, since it's the only one your user name is good on.  If you are a global user you will see a list of ezboards that you have designated as favorites.  <br>
<br>
If you are an ezSupporter you will also see your most recent posts as well as a list of the last 5 boards that you have visited.<br>
<br>
Everyone will see these links<br>
<br>
View Profile| Edit Profile | Account Preferences <br>
<br>
These are the links that you use to set your preferences.<br>
<br>
View profile lets you see what others see when they look at your porfile.<br>
<br>
Edit profile lets you change what is seen<br>
<br>
Account Preferences lets you change some ezboard settings.<br>
<br>
There is also a quick jump field that lets you go directly to any ezboard as long as you know the board ID (the Ape Vine is brattlersden)<br>
<br>
If you are an ezSupporter you will also have a place to manage any linked accounts.<br>
<br>
