he my account page.  How do I add a board to my favorites?<br>
<br>
A: There are a couple of ways.  Many boards (such as this one will have an &quot;Add to my favorites&quot; link at the bottom of the main page.  Just click on it.  Once you've done that the link will disappear.<br>
<br>
Some boards have added some kind of custom work to the footer and lose the usual links.  If there is no add favorites link, just copy the web ID and go to your control center and at the bottom of your favorites list is a Managing my favorites link.  From there you get a screen where you can add and delete boards from your list.<br>
<br>
To add the board, just type in the web ID.  To delete, check the board(s) you want deleted and hit the button at the bottom of the page.<br>
<br>
Q:  Where do I get a boards web ID?<br>
<br>
A:  From the main page of any board, look at the URL.  The ID is the part right after ezboard.com/  For the Ape Vine the ID is brattlersden. ALL IDs start with b (ezboard uses b for board and f for forum in its URLs).  The ID for Stormy's board is bnekkidamazonhockey.<br>
<br>
Q: I bookmark my favorite boards with my browser, why would I want to make them favorites with ezboard?<br>
<br>
A: I have my most visited boards bookmarked in IE as well.  But what happens if your computer crashes and you lose your bookmarks? Or your visiting your grandmother in Austin?  This way you always have access to your favorites<br>
<br>
Q:  I visit boards from the ezboard ring, do I need to make them favorites as well?<br>
<br>
A: It's not a bad idea.  You never know,  I might get mad at the ezop of one the boards that you visit from time to time and remove them from the ring.  Or I might decide that I find the content of a particular board inappropriate.  <br>
<br>
Q: Any other reasons I might want to add a board to favorites?<br>
<br>
A:  Sometimes I'll run across a board that looks interesting, but I don't have time to really check it out to see if I like it.  I'll add to favorites to be checked out later.  When I have time I'll look it over and decide if it stays on my personal list, if it needs to be added to the ezboard ring or if it should be deleted.  I've even saved a couple that I thought a family member might like. Saved it until I could pass it one, then deleted it (like the Pokemon board).<br>
<br>
